      • locateLineUp

        public java.lang.String locateLineUp(int frills,
                                     int forwards,
                                     int defenses)
        Name: locateLineUp
        This method allows to locate the soccer players on the court according the line up created.
        Post: The players have been located on the court.
        Parameters:
        frills - int. Amount of frills on the court. frills mayor o =0 Y frills menor o=7.
        forwards - int. Amount of forwards on the court. forwards mayor o =0 Y forwards menor o =7.
        defenses - int. Amount of defenses on the court. defenses mayor o =0 Y defenses menor o =7.
        Returns:
        message String. Message that show the matrix with the line up of the players.
